  "text": "In this paper, I have attempted to show that it is possible to think about unconscious communication and to illuminate some of the limits and the challenges entailed. I have echoed [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] in arguing that qualitative researchers already use ideas like \"rapport\" that rely implicitly on psychoanalysis. Paying attention to an interviewee's repetition of a particular concern, I have illustrated how unconscious \"excess\" may present itself in ways that are relatively straightforward and uncontentious to trace using the idea of the receptive unconscious. In so doing I have sought to show how researchers might utilise psychoanalytic ideas to help illuminate otherwise elusive but nevertheless ordinary features of the interactions that constitute interviews, like the variably successful unconscious negotiation of trust.",
